         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Garden Melbourne, ¶ 11/12/72 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to solicit that you will be pleased to sanction the transfer of the sum of £74.10/— from the vote Reward to orphan-boys employed in the...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.12.11</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Casey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">G72/26909, unit 750, VPRS 44 inward registered and unregistered correspondence, VA 538 Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written by Georg Luehmann and signed by M.</p>
               </note>Botanic Garden Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">11/12/72</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to solicit that you will be pleased to sanction the transfer of the sum of £74.10/— from the vote Reward to orphan-boys employed in the Botanic Garden to the vote for Wages. My original estimate for the former item was £91.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>- .<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the Botanic Garden and the Reserves together; when the division took place one half that sum, viz £45.10/—, was provided for Govt. House Domain, and, through some misunderstanding I presume, £120.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>- .<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>were voted<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for this item for the Botan. Garden.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>under Department of Agricuture in vote for Commissioner of Crown Lands and Survey in record of meeting of the Legislative Assembly,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>4 September, 1872 (Victoria,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Votes and proceedings of the Legislative Assembly</seg>, Session 1872, vol. 1,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p.170) The amended estimates had been tabled in the Assembly on 29 August, ordered to be printed and referred to the Committee of Supply,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(p. 162).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>As the whole of this sum will not be required for this purpose, I respectfully request that the above named transfer may be granted, as I shall by this means be enabled to retain the services of gardener Morrison for the ensuing seven months.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to refer to my letter of 3rd inst.,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. Casey, 3 December 1872.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>wherein I had the honor to point out, that the amount available for "Stores" &amp;c would be insufficient to meet the requirements of the Department, and I have now again the honor to request, that the desired sum of £110.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>may be placed at my disposal, to cover<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unavoidable</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>expenditure for Forage for the carthorse, Coal for engine &amp; conservatories, Fence-Wire and Calico for plant sheds, Paper and Bisulphide of Carbon for the Museum Bricks for gutters, timber for repairs, paint and other necessaries, urgently needed.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Direct. botan. Garden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">In regard to gardener Morrison I beg to refer also to my letter of 3rd inst.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Honorable the Commissioner of Lands<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's letter was referred to the Secretary of Agriculture, A. Wallis, on 13 December 1872, but the file does not indicate any other action.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
